title: Ken Burns - Baseball - Inning3 (The Faith Of Fifty Million Peopl
description:
Before and After WW1, a steady stream of immigrants lands on the shores of America. To pursue the American dream. To play the American game

But even as thousands of new Americans pick up a ball for the first time, even as the endures a world war, baseball is trying to endure a decade that includes the meanest, vilest, angriest player ever to step onto a field ans a scandal that almost destroys the game.

Approx. 120 mins.
